definition.value: A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is 7-hydroxyisoflavone substituted by a methoxy group at position 4'.
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as benzoyl.
A primary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of kynuramine resulting from the protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Product of the enzymatic  deamination of kynuramine.
A propanal having an amino substituent at the 3-position

A member of the class of piperazines that is piperazine substituted by a carboxy group at position 2R and a (1E)-1-phosphonoprop-1-en-3-yl group at position 4. It is an antagonist of N-methyl-D-aspartate receptors (NMDARs) and was in clinical development by Novartis for the treatment of cognition disorders and brain injuries (now discontinued).
The maleic acid salt of Ro 25-6981. It is a potent and selective antagonist of GluN2B-containing NMDA receptors.

A dihydropyridine that is 1,4-dihydropyridine substituted by a methyl, {2-[benzyl(methyl)amino]ethoxy}carbonyl, 3-nitrophenyl, methoxycarbonyl and methyl groups at positions 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6, respectively.
A class of terpenoids formed in plants in response to fungal infection, physical damage, chemical injury, or a pathogenic process.
An alkane-alpha,omega-diamine that is putrescine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2.
